HEADWORD: Dowle
<hw>Dowle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>douille</ets> soft. Cf. <er>Ductile</er>.]</ety> <def>Feathery or
wool-like down; filament of a feather.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No feather, or <qex>dowle</qex> of a feather.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Down</ent>⟦br⟧
